  "text": "The clinical and prognostic significance of microemboli in patients with atrial fibrillation and prosthetic valves is unclear. Only few studies have shown that anticoagulation may reduce microembolic frequency in patients with atrial fibrillation [CITATION_1] . It is difficult to choose between anticoagulation versus anti-platelet agents based on the presence or absence of microemboli. However, the presence of microemboli may prompt the use either anticoagulation or anti-platelet agents in patients with atrial fibrillation regardless of any thromboembolic events.",
